Prepare rice as directed on package. Meanwhile, thaw shrimp as directed on package; remove tails. Spread cooked rice in 13x9-inch baking dish. Place in refrigerator 15 minutes to cool. Toss with 1/4 cup of the dressing. Refrigerate until completely cooled, about 15 minutes more. Toss cooled rice with shrimp, basil, onions and remaining dressing. Pour out onto serving platter. Garnish with lime wedges.